      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SAFE HUSTLE (5) is better than he's shown his past couple, with his prior form stacking right up. The better draw today is a big tick and he should be close to the speed, which is how she ran her best efforts. Can return to winning ways. PRINCE RAGNAR (1) led them up last start over 1217m at Geraldton and felt the pinch late. Back to 1100m today is a big tick and the claim of Cheung comes in handy. Back in grade and can be tough to beat.  LOVA SESSION (3) is returning from a spell of 12 weeks. Finished sixth at Belmont Park over 1200m at the first run last prep. Now with a new trainer Peter Bamford. One of the genuine hopes in the race. SIMPLY ROSSO (2) raced on the pace to the bend before fading to finish ninth, beaten 5 lengths, over this journey at Geraldton. Should give a bold sight. TALKING HEADS (6) won't be far away.",
